<HL>
   Business Brief -- Bonneville Pacific Corp:
   Portland General Agrees
   To Buy Up to 49% Stake
</HL>
<DATE>
09/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10
</SO>
<CO>
   PGN BPCO
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
</IN>
<LP>
   Portland General Corp. has signed a definitive agreement
to acquire as much as 49% of the common stock of Bonneville
Pacific Corp., an independent energy, food processing and
waste management concern, for about $34 million.
   Portland General, an energy holding company in Portland,
Ore., will buy a $10 million debenture convertible into 1.3
million Bonneville common shares at $7.50 a share; 3.3
million new common shares at $6 each; and warrants
outstanding at $1 each to buy four million additional common
shares at $6 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Also, Portland General has the option to acquire
additional common stock to raise its stake to the 49% total.
Richard G. Reiten, Portland General's president, said the
agreement is part of the company's efforts to build up its
independent power business. The transaction is expected to
close in mid-October.
</TEXT>
